result.execSummary:
Darwin O Moody was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Darwin O Moody was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Per Waushara County Jail - Transport to Mississippi has been scheduled for the DE. STC removed from the calendar.
Request to Court regarding Extradition - Will be addressed in hearing on 4/4/2022
Status conference on April 4, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
Letter to Court regarding awaited Extradition

Case called @ 1:15 PM Defendant Darwin O Moody appeared by video, in custody. Attorney Wesley Kottke appeared in court for State of Wisconsin. Hearing to address the defendant's extradition to the State of Mississippi. Defendant waives his right to be personally present in the courtroom. Defendant advised of his right to counsel. Defendant waives his right to counsel. Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by the Court. Defendant does not contest the extradition and will voluntarily waive. Defendant advises that the DOB on the complaint is not correct. Correct DOB is 10/10/1980. The Court accepts the voluntary waiver of the extradition. The DE signs the waiver and consent form in the presence of the Court and enters and Order for Extradition to the State of Mississippi.
